column1: On December 1, 2014, the Federal Reserve conducted a fixed-rate offering of term deposits through its Term Deposit Facility. The operation offered seven-day term deposits at an interest rate of 0.30000 percent. Following are the results of the operation:
column9: The awarded deposits will settle on December 4, 2014, and will mature on December 11, 2014. The interest rate of 0.30000 percent will apply to all awarded deposits.
